@pdomansk are you using PowerShell Core 6.0.0-beta.9 on windows when you see that, or Windows PowerShell 5.1?

Windows PowerShell 5.1 used Internet explorer to parse HTML for ` HtmlWebResponseObject.ParsedHtml` objects . 

PowerShell Core always returns a `BasicHtmlWebResponseObject` and currently only supports basic parsing as it does not use Internet Explorer. The `ParsedHtml` property should be null on both Windows and Linux in PowerShell Core 6.0.0.
